devdoc.author: Fabian Vogelsteller <fabian@lukso.network>
devdoc.details: Implementation of a contract module which provides the ability to call arbitrary functions at any other smart contract and itself, including using `delegatecall`, `staticcall` as well creating contracts using `create` and `create2` This is the basis for a smart contract based account system, but could also be used as a proxy account system

execute(uint256,address,uint256,bytes).details: Executes any other smart contract. SHOULD only be callable by the owner of the contract set via ERC173 Emits a {Executed} event, when a call is executed under `operationType` 0, 3 and 4 Emits a {ContractCreated} event, when a contract is created under `operationType` 1 and 2

params.data: The call data, or the bytecode of the contract to deploy
params.operationType: The operation to execute: CALL = 0 CREATE = 1 CREATE2 = 2 STATICCALL = 3 DELEGATECALL = 4
params.to: The smart contract or address to interact with, `to` will be unused if a contract is created (operation 1 and 2)
params.value: The amount of native tokens to transfer (in Wei).

initialized().details: Returns that the contract has been initialized.

initializing().details: Returns that the contract is in the process of being initialized.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Deployable Proxy Implementation of ERC725 X Executor

ContractCreated(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Emitted when a contract is created

initialize(address).notice: Sets the owner of the contract
